[SN]TITLE[SN]
US football team Pittsburgh Steelers take on robot players

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
American football team the Pittsburgh Steelers are using robots in their training sessions.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
24 May 2016 Last updated at 09:30 BST
The robotic dummies are controlled by another team member from the sidelines.
It's claimed the high-tech robots can accurately copy the movements of an opposing player on the field.
This means the team can practise their tackles and touchdowns, whilst legging it away from a robot dummy!
